BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --TRT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Name of Treatment
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: The topic for the intervention observation, usually the verbatim name of the treatment, drug, medicine, or therapy given during the dosing interval for the observation.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --MODIFY
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Modified Treatment Name
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: If the value for --TRT is modified for coding purposes, then the modified text is placed here.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DECOD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Standardized Treatment Name
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Standardized or dictionary-Derived name of the topic variable, --TRT, or the modified topic variable (--MODIFY), if applicable. Equivalent to the generic drug name in WHO Drug, or a term in SNOMED, ICD9, or other published or sponsor-defined dictionaries.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --CAT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Category
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to define a category of topic-variable values.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SCAT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Subcategory
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to define a further categorization of --CAT values.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --PRESP
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Pre-specified
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used when a specific intervention is pre-specified on a CRF. Values should be "Y" or null.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --OCCUR
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Occurrence
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to record whether a pre-specified intervention occurred when information about the occurrence of a specific intervention is solicited.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STAT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Completion Status
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to indicate when a question about the occurrence of a pre-specified intervention was not answered. Should be null or have a value of NOT DONE.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --REASND
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Reason Not Done
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Reason not done. Used in conjunction with --STAT when value is NOT DONE.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --INDC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Indication
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Denotes the indication for the intervention (e.g., why the therapy was taken or administered).

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --CLAS
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Class
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Class for a medication or treatment, often obtained from a coding dictionary.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --CLASCD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Class Code
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to represent code for --CLAS.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DOSE
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Dose
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Amount of --TRT given. Not populated when --DOSTXT is populated.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DOSTXT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Dose Description
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Dosing information collected in text form. Examples: <1 per day, 200-400. Not populated when --DOSE is populated.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DOSU
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Dose Units
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Units for --DOSE, --DOSTOT, or --DOSTXT (Examples: ng, mg, mg/kg).

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DOSFRM
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Dose Form
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Dose form for the treatment. Examples: TABLET, CAPSULE.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DOSFRQ
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Dosing Frequency per Interval
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Usually expressed as the number of doses given per a specific interval. Examples: QD, BID, TID, QID.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DOSTOT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Total Daily Dose
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Total daily dose of --TRT using the units in --DOSU. Used when dosing is collected as Total Daily Dose.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Derived based on --DOSE and --DOSFRQ

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DOSRGM
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Intended Dose Regimen
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Text description of the (intended) schedule or regimen for the Intervention. Examples: TWO WEEKS ON, TWO WEEKS OFF.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ROUTE
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Route of Administration
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Route of administration for the intervention. Examples: ORAL, INTRAVENOUS.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --LOT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Lot Number
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Lot number for the intervention described in --TRT.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --LOC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Location of Dose Administration
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Anatomical location of an intervention, such as an injection site. Example: RIGHT ARM for an injection.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --TRTV
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Treatment Vehicle
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Vehicle for administration of treatment, such as a liquid in which the treatment drug is dissolved. Example: SALINE.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --VAMT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Treatment Vehicle Amount
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Amount of the treatment vehicle administered or given.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --VAMTU
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Treatment Vehicle Amount Units
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Units for the treatment vehicle. Examples: mL, mg.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ADJ
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Reason for Dose Adjustment
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Describes reason or explanation of why a dose is adjusted. Examples ADVERSE EVENT, INSUFFICIENT RESPONSE, NON-MEDICAL REASON.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --TERM
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Reported Term
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Topic variable for an event observation, which is the verbatim or pre-specified name of the event.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --MODIFY
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Modified Reported Term
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: If the value for --TERM is modified for coding purposes, then the modified text is placed here.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --LLT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Lowest Level Term
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: MedDRA Lowest Level Term.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: MedDRA version 13.1

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --LLTCD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Lowest Level Term Code
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: MedDRA Lowest Level Term code.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: MedDRA version 13.1

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DECOD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Dictionary-Derived Term
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Dictionary or sponsor-defined Derived text description of the topic variable, --TERM, or the modified topic variable (--MODIFY), if applicable. Equivalent to the Preferred Term (PT in MedDRA).
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: MedDRA version 13.1

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --PTCD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Preferred Term Code
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: MedDRA Preferred Term code.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: MedDRA version 13.1

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --HLT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: High Level Term
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: MedDRA High Level Term from the primary path.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: MedDRA version 13.1

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --HLTCD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: High Level Term Code
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: MedDRA High Level Term code from the primary path.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: MedDRA version 13.1

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --HLGT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: High Level Group Term
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: MedDRA High Level Group Term from the primary path.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: MedDRA version 13.1

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --HLGTCD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: High Level Group Term Code
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: MedDRA High Level Group Term code from the primary path.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: MedDRA version 13.1

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --CAT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Category
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to define a category of topic-variable values.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SCAT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Subcategory
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to define a further categorization of --CAT values.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --PRESP
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Pre-specified
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to indicate whether the event described by --TERM was pre-specified on a CRF. Value is Y for pre-specified events, null for spontaneously reported events.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --OCCUR
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Occurrence
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to record whether a pre-specified event occurred when information about the occurrence of a specific event is solicited.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STAT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Completion Status
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to indicate when a question about the occurrence of a pre-specified event was not answered. Should be null or have a value of NOT DONE.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --REASND
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Reason Not Done
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Reason not done. Used in conjunction with --STAT when its value is NOT DONE.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --BODSYS
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Body System or Organ Class
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Body system or system organ class from a standard hierarchy (e.g. MedDRA) associated with an event. Example: GASTROINTESTINAL DISORDERS.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: MedDRA version 13.1

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --BDSYCD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Body System or Organ Class Code
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: MedDRA System Organ Class code used for analysis.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: MedDRA version 13.1

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SOC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Primary System Organ Class
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: MedDRA primary System Organ Class.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: MedDRA version 13.1

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SOCCD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Primary System Organ Class Code
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: MedDRA primary System Organ Class code.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: MedDRA version 13.1

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --LOC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Location of Event
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Describes anatomical location relevant for the event. Example: LEFT ARM for skin rash.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SEV
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Severity/Intensity
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: The severity or intensity of the event. Examples: MILD, MODERATE, SEVERE.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SER
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Serious Event
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Is this is a serious event? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ACN
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Action Taken with Study Treatment
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Describes changes made to the study treatment as a result of the event. Examples: DOSE INCREASED, DOSE NOT CHANGED.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ACNOTH
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Other Action Taken
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Describes other actions taken as a result of the event that are unrelated to dose adjustments of study treatment.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --REL
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Causality
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Records the investigator's opinion as to the causality of the event to the treatment. ICH E2A and E2B examples include NOT RELATED, UNLIKELY RELATED, POSSIBLY RELATED, RELATED.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --RELNST
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Relationship to Non-Study Treatment
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: An opinion as to whether the event may have been due to a treatment other than study drug. Example: "MORE LIKELY RELATED TO ASPIRIN USE."

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --PATT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Pattern of Event
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to indicate the pattern of the event over time. Examples: INTERMITTENT, CONTINUOUS, SINGLE EVENT.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --OUT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Outcome of Event
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Description of the outcome of an event. Examples: RECOVERED/RESOLVED, FATAL.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SCAN
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Involves Cancer
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Was the event associated with the development of cancer? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SCONG
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Congenital Anomaly or Birth Defect
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Was the event associated with congenital anomaly or birth defect? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SDISAB
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Persist or Signif Disability/Incapacity
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Did the event result in persistent or significant disability/incapacity? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SDTH
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Results in Death
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Did the event result in death? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SHOSP
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Requires or Prolongs Hospitalization
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Did the event require or prolong hospitalization? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SLIFE
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Is Life Threatening
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Was the event life threatening? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SOD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Occurred with Overdose
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Did the event occur with an overdose? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SMIE
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Other Medically Important Serious Event
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Do additional categories for seriousness apply? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --CONTRT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Concomitant or Additional Trtmnt Given
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Was another treatment given because of the occurrence of the event? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --TOX
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Toxicity
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Description of toxicity quantified by --TOXGR such as NCI CTCAE Short Name. Examples: HYPERCALCEMIA, HYPOCALCEMIA. Sponsor should specify which scale and version is used in the Sponsor Comments column of the Define.xml document.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Derived based on AECTC V4.0

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --TOXGR
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Toxicity Grade
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Records toxicity grade using a standard toxicity scale (such as the NCI CTCAE). Sponsor should specify which scale and version is used in the Sponsor Comments column of the Define.xml document.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Derived based on AECTC V4.0

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --TESTCD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Short Name of Measurement, Test or Exam
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Short character value for --TEST used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical format to a horizontal format. The short value can be up to 8 characters. Examples: PLAT, SYSBP, RRMIN, EYEEXAM.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --TEST
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Name of Measurement, Test or Exam
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Long name For --TESTCD. Examples: Platelet, Systolic Blood Pressure, Summary (Min) RR Duration, Eye Examination.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --MODIFY
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Modified Term
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: If the value of --ORRES is modified for coding purposes, then the modified text is placed here.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --OBJ
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Object of the Observation
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used in domains modeled as Findings About Events or Findings About Interventions. Describes the event or intervention whose property is being measured in --TESTCD/--TEST. Example: an event of vomiting which has findings, where --OBJ = "VOMIT" and the volume of VOMIT is being measured where --TESTCD = "VOLUME".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --CAT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Category
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to define a category of topic-variable values. Examples: HEMATOLOGY, URINALYSIS, CHEMISTRY, HAMILTON DEPRESSION SCALE, SF36.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SCAT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Subcategory
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to define a further categorization of --CAT values. Example: DIFFERENTIAL.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --POS
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Position of Subject During Observation
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Position of the subject during a measurement or examination. Examples: SUPINE, STANDING, SITTING.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --BODSYS
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Body System or Organ Class
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Body System or Organ Class that is involved for a finding from the standard hierarchy for dictionary-coded results. Example: MedDRA SOC.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ORRES
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Result or Finding in Original Units
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Result of the measurement or finding as originally received or collected. Examples: 120, <1, POS.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ORRESU
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Original Units
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Unit for --ORRES. Examples: IN, LB, kg/L.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ORNRLO
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Normal Range Lower Limit-Original Units
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Lower end of normal range or reference range for results stored in --ORRES.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ORNRHI
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Normal Range Upper Limit-Original Units
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Upper end of normal range or reference range for results stored in --ORRES.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STRESC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Character Result/Finding in Std Format
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Contains the result value for all findings, copied or Derived from --ORRES in a standard format or in standard units. --STRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in --STRESN. For example, if various tests have results "NONE", "NEG", and "NEGATIVE" in --ORRES and these results effectively have the same meaning, they could be represented in standard format in --STRESC as "NEGATIVE".
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: If data collected in non-standard units, then data is converted using standard conversion factors to standard units; else equal to --ORRES.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STRESN
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from --STRESC. --STRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Equal to numeric value of --STRESC

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STRESU
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Standard Units
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Standardized units used for --STRESC and --STRESN. Example: mol/L.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STNRLO
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Normal Range Lower Limit-Standard Units
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Lower end of normal range or reference range for standardized results (e.g., --STRESC, --STRESN) represented in standardized units (--STRESU).
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: If data collected in non-standard units, then --ORNRLO is converted using standard conversion factors to standard units; else equal to numeric value of --ORNRLO.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STNRHI
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Normal Range Upper Limit-Standard Units
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Upper end of normal range or reference range for standardized results (e.g., --STRESC, --STRESN) represented in standardized units (--STRESU).
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: If data collected in non-standard units, then --ORNRHI is converted using standard conversion factors to standard units; else equal to numeric value of --ORNRHI.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STNRC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Reference Range for Char Rslt-Std Units
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: For normal range or reference range values for results stored in --STRESC that are character in ordinal or categorical scale. Example: Negative to Trace.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --NRIND
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Normal/Reference Range Indicator
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to indicate the value is outside the normal range or reference range. May be defined by --ORNRLO and --ORNRHI or other objective criteria. Examples: Y, N; HIGH, LOW; NORMAL; ABNORMAL.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Reference Range Indicator based upon standard results and ranges.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --RESCAT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Result Category
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to categorize the result of a finding. Example: MALIGNANT or BENIGN for tumor findings.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STAT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Completion Status
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to indicate that a question was not asked or a test was not done, or a test was attempted but did not generate a result. Should be null or have a value of NOT DONE.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --REASND
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Reason Not Done
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Reason not done. Used in conjunction with --STAT when value is NOT DONE.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --XFN
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: External File Path
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Filename for an external file, such as one for an ECG waveform or a medical image.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --NAM
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Laboratory/Vendor Name
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Name or identifier of the vendor (e.g., laboratory) that provided the test results.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --LOINC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: LOINC Code
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Logical Observation Identifiers Names and Codes (LOINC) code for the topic variable such as a lab test.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SPEC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Specimen Material Type
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Defines the type of specimen used for a measurement. Examples: SERUM, PLASMA, URINE.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ANTREG
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Anatomical Region
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Defines the specific anatomical or biological region of a tissue, organ specimen or the region from which the specimen is obtained, as defined in the Protocol, such as a section or part of what is described in the --SPEC variable. Examples: CORTEX,MEDULLA, MUCOSA

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SPCCND
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Specimen Condition
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Defines the condition of the specimen. Example: CLOUDY.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SPCUFL
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Specimen Usability for the Test
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Describes the usability of the specimen for the test. The value will be N if the specimen is not usable, and null if the specimenis usable.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --LOC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Location Used for the Measurement
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Location relevant to the collection of the measurement. Example: RECTAL for temperature, LEFT ARM for blood pressure or V1 for an ECG lead.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --LAT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Laterality
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Qualifier for anatomical location or specimen further detailing laterality

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DIR
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Directionality
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Qualifier for anatomical location or specimen further detailing directionality

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --PORTOT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Portion or Totality
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Qualifier for anatomical location or specimen further detailing the distribution, which means arrangement of, apportioning of.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --METHOD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Method of Test or Examination
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Method of the test or examination. Examples: EIA (Enzyme Immunoassay), ELECTROPHORESIS, DIPSTICK.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --LEAD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Lead Identified to Collect Measurements
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Lead or leads identified to capture the measurement for a testfrom an instrument. Examples: LEAD I, LEAD V2, LEAD CM5.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --CSTATE
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Consciousness State
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: The consciousness state of the subject at the time of measurement. Examples: CONSCIOUS, SEMI-CONSCIOUS,UNCONSCIOUS

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --BLFL
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Baseline Flag
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Indicator used to identify a baseline value. Should be Y or null.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Derivation of baseline: Safety subjects only: --BLFL=Y for last non missing record on or before the first dose date (RFSTDTC).

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --FAST
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Fasting Status
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Indicator used to identify fasting status. Valid values include Y, N, U or null if not relevant.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DRVFL
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Derived Flag
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to indicate a Derived record (e.g., a record that represents the average of other records such as a computed baseline). Should be Y or null.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --EVAL
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Evaluator
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Role of the person who provided the evaluation. Used only for results that are subjective (e.g., Assigned by a person or a group). Examples: ADJUDICATION COMMITTEE, VENDOR.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --EVALID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Evaluator Specified
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: The Evaluator Specified variable is used in conjunction with TUEVAL to provide an additional level of detail.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ACPTFL
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Accepted Record Flag
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: In cases where more than one independent assessor (e.g. RADIOLOGIST 1 & RADIOLOGIST 2) provide independent assessments at the same time point this flag identifies the record that is considered to be the accepted assessment.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --TOX
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Toxicity
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Description of toxicity quantified by --TOXGR such as NCI CTCAE Short Name. Examples: HYPERCALCEMIA, HYPOCALCEMIA. Sponsor should specify which scale and version is used in the Sponsor Comments column of the Define.xml document.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Derived from results and reference range based on AECTC V4.0

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --TOXGR
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Toxicity Grade
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Records toxicity grade using a standard toxicity scale (such as the NCI CTCAE). Sponsor should specify which scale and version is used in the Sponsor Comments column of the Define data definition document.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Derived from results and reference range based on AECTC V4.0

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SEV
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Severity
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Describes the severity or intensity of a particular finding. Examples: MILD, MODERATE, SEVERE.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DTHREL
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Relationship to Death
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Describes the relationship of a particular finding to the death of a subject.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --LLOQ
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Lower Limit of Quantitation
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Indicates the lower limit of quantitation for an assay. Units will be those used for --STRESU.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --EXCLFL
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Exclude from Statistics
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Indicates whether the values in the result variables for this record should be excluded from summary statistical calculations such as Mean, Standard Deviation, and Count (and others). Expected to be Y or null. --EXCLFL should not be used when --STAT is NOT DONE. Not to be used with human clinical trials.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --REASEX
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Reason for Exclusion from Statistics
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Reason excluded from statistics. Used in conjunction with --EXCLFL when its value is Y. Not to be used with human clinical trials

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: SUBJID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Subject Identifier for the Study
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Subject identifier, which must be unique within the study. Often the ID of the subject as recorded on a CRF.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: RFSTDTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Subject Reference Start Date/Time
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Reference Start Date/time for the subject in ISO 8601 character format. Usually equivalent to date/time when subject was first exposed to study treatment. Required for all randomized subjects; will be null for all subjects who did not meet the milestone the date requires, such as screen failures or unAssigned subjects.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: For safety subjects equal to first date/time of study drug. Null for subjects who did not take study drug.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: RFENDTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Subject Reference End Date/Time
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Reference End Date/time for the subject in ISO 8601 character format. Usually equivalent to the date/time when subject was determined to have ended the trial, and often equivalent to date/time of last exposure to study treatment. Required for all randomized subjects; null for screen failures or unAssigned subjects.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: For safety subjects equal to last date/time of study drug. Null for subjects who did not take study drug.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: RFXSTDTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Date/Time of First Study Treatment
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: First date of exposure to any Protocol-specified treatment or therapy for the subject in ISO 8601 character format.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Equal to first date/time of study drug. Null for subjects who did not take study drug.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: RFXENDTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Date/Time of Last Study Treatment
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Last date of exposure to any Protocol-specified treatment or therapy for the subject in ISO 8601 character format.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Equal to last date/time of study drug. Null for subjects who did not take study drug.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: RFICDTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Date/Time of Informed Consent
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Date/time of informed consent in ISO 8601 character format.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: RFPENDTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Date/Time of End of Participation
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Date/time when subject ended participation or follow-up in a trial, in ISO 8601 character format. Should correspond to the last known date of contact.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Last known date of contact

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: DTHDTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Date/Time of Death
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Date/time of death for any subject who died, in ISO 8601 format. Should represent the date/time that is captured in the clinical-trial database.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: DTHFL
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Subject Death Flag
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Indicates the subject died. Should be Y or null. Should be populated even when the death date is unknown.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: SITEID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Study Site Identifier
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Unique identifier for a site within a study.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: INVID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Investigator Identifier
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: An identifier to describe the Investigator for the study. May be used in addition to the SITEID. Not needed if SITEID is equivalent to INVID.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: INVNAM
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Investigator Name
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Name of the investigator for a site.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: BRTHDTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Date/Time of Birth
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Date/time of birth of the subject in ISO 8601 character format.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: AGE
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Age
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Age expressed in AGEU. May be Derived as (RFSTDTC-BRTHDTC), but BRTHDTC may not be available in all cases (due to subject privacy concerns).
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Year part of (RFICDTC - BRTHDTC)

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: AGEU
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Age Units
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Units associated with AGE.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: SEX
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Sex
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Sex of the subject.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: RACE
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Race
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Race of the subject. Sponsors should refer to "Collection of Race and Ethnicity Data in Clinical Trials" (FDA, September 2005) for guidance regarding the collection of race .

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: ETHNIC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Ethnicity
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: The ethnicity of the subject. Sponsors should refer to "Collection of Race and Ethnicity Data in Clinical Trials" (FDA, September 2005) for guidance regarding the collection of ethnicity.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: ARMCD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Planned Arm Code
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: ARMCD is limited to 20 characters and does not have special character restrictions.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: ARM
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Description of Planned Arm
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Name of the Arm to which the subject was Assigned.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: ACTARMCD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Actual Arm Code
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Short name for the actual Arm in which the subject participated during the trial, limited to 20 characters.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Derived from arm code in Trial Arm (TA) based on Actual Assignment.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: ACTARM
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Description of Actual Arm
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Description of the actual Arm in which the subject participated during thetrial.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Derived from description of arm in TRIAL ARM (TA) based on Actual Assignment.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: COUNTRY
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Country
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Country of the investigational site at which the subject participated in the trial in ISO 3166 three-character format.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: RDOMAIN
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Related Domain Abbreviation
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Domain Abbreviation of the parent record(s). Null for records collected on general comments or additional information CRF page.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: IDVAR
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Identifying Variable
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Identifying variable in the parent dataset that identifies the record(s) to which the comment applies. Examples AESEQ or CMGRPID. Used only when individual comments are related to domain records. Null for comments collected on separate CRFs.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: IDVARVAL
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Identifying Variable Value
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Value of identifying variable of the parent record(s). Null for comments collected on separate CRFs.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --UPDES
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Description of Unplanned Element
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Description of what happened to the subject during an unplanned Element. Used only if ETCD has the value of "UNPLAN".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: COREF
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Comment Reference
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Sponsor-defined reference associated with the comment. May be the CRF page number (e.g. 650), or a module name (e.g. DEMOG), or a combination of information that identifies the reference (e.g. 650-VITALS-VISIT 2).

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: COVAL
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Comment
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: The text of the comment. Text over 200 characters can be added to additional columns COVAL1-COVALn.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: COEVAL
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Evaluator
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Used to describe the originator of the comment. Example: CENTRAL REVIEWER.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: ETCD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Subject Element Code
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: ETCD (the companion to ELEMENT) is limited to 8 characters and does not have special character restrictions. These values should be short for ease of use in programming, but it is not expected that ETCD will need to serve as a variable name.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: ELEMENT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Description of Subject Element
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: The name of the Element. If ETCD has a value of "UNPLAN" then ELEMENT should be Null.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: SESTDTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Start Date/Time of Element
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Start date/time for an Element for each subject, represented in ISO 8601 character format.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: SEENDTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: End Date/Time of Element
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: End date/time of an Element for each subject, represented in ISO 8601 character format.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: SEUPDES
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Description of Unplanned Element
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Description of what happened to the subject during an unplanned Element. Used only if ETCD has the value of "UNPLAN".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: IDVAR
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Identifying Variable
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Identifying variable in the dataset that identifies the related record(s). Examples: --SEQ and --GRPID.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: IDVARVAL
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Identifying Variable Value
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Value of identifying variable of the related parent record(s). Used only when individual records are being related.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: RELTYPE
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Relationship Type
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Identifying the hierarchical level of the records in the relationship. Values must be either ONE or MANY. Used only when datasets are being related.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: RELID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Relationship Identifier
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Unique value within a USUBJID that identifies the relationship. All records for the same USUBJID that have the same RELID are considered ‘related/associated.’ RELID can be any value the sponsor chooses, and is only meaningful within the RELREC dataset to identify the related/associated Domain records.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: STUDYID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Study Identifier
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Study Identifier of the domain record(s).

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: RDOMAIN
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Related Domain Abbreviation
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Two-character abbreviation for the domain of the parent record(s).

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: USUBJID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Unique Subject Identifier
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Concatenate STUDYID, SITEID and SUBJID, separated by "-".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --UPDES
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Description of Unplanned Visit
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Description of what happened to the subject during an unplanned visit. Null for Protocol-defined visits.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: ARMCD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Planned Arm Code
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Short 8-character version of ARM, used for programming.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: ARM
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Description of Planned Arm
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Name given to Arm or treatment group.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: ETCD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Element Code
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Short 8-character name for ELEMENT, used for programming. If an encountered Element differs from the planned ELEMENT to the point that it is considered a new ELEMENT, then use UNPLAN as the value for ETCD to represent this Element.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: ELEMENT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Description of Element
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: The name of the Element. If an encountered Element differs from the planned ELEMENT to the point that it is considered a new ELEMENT, then ELEMENT should be null.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: STUDYID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Study Identifier
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Unique identifier for a study.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: DOMAIN
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Domain Abbreviation
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Two-character abbreviation for the domain most relevant to the observation. The Domain abbreviation is also used as a prefix for variables to ensure uniqueness when datasets are merged.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: RDOMAIN
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Related Domain Abbreviation
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Domain Abbreviation of the parent record(s).

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: USUBJID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Unique Subject Identifier
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Concatenate STUDYID, SITEID and SUBJID, separated by "-".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: POOLID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Pool Identifier
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: An identifier used to identify a result from a group of subjects that is notassignable to a specific subject.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: UDEVID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Generic Device Identifier
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: General name for a device.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: UPRODID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Unique Device Identifier
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Unique identifier for a specific device or collection of devices.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SEQ
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Sequence Number
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Sequence number to ensure uniqueness of records within a dataset for a subject (or within a parameter, in the case of the Trial Summary domain). May be any valid number (including decimals) and does not have to start at 1. Should be Assigned to be in a consistent chronological order.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Sort by the key variables specified in the domain list. Assign --SEQ=1 to the first record and increment --SEQ by 1 for each additional record so that --SEQ is unique for each record within a USUBJID.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --GRPID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Group ID
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Optional group identifier, used to link together a block of related records within a subject in a domain. Also used to link together a block of related records in the Trial Summary dataset.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --REFID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Reference ID
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Optional internal or external identifier such as lab specimen ID, or UUID for an ECG waveform or a medical image.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --SPID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Sponsor-Defined Identifier
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Sponsor-defined identifier. Example: pre-printed line identifier on a Concomitant Medications page.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --LNKID
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Link ID
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Identifier used to link a feature (such as a tumor) initially recorded as a result in one findings domain to assessments of that feature in another findings domain. This may be a one-to-one or a one-to-many relationship. For Example: A single tumor may have multiple measurements/assessment performed at each study visit.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --LNKGRP
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Link Group ID
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: A grouping identifier used to identify a group of assessment results in one domain that are evaluated, as a group, and contribute to a (summary) result in another domain. This will usually be a many-to-one relationship. For example: Multiple tumor measurements/assessments will contribute to a single response to therapy determination record.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: VISITNUM
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Visit Number
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Clinical encounter number. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: VISIT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Visit Name
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Protocol-defined description of a clinical encounter.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: VISITDY
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Planned Study Day of Visit
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Planned study day of VISIT. Should be an integer.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: TAETORD
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Planned Order of Elements within Arm
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Number that gives the planned order of the Element within the Arm.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: EPOCH
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Epoch
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Epoch associated with the start date/time of the observation, or the date/time of collection if start date/time is not collected.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: 'SCREENING' if date of findings or start date of events/interventions is before RFSTDTC; 'TREATMENT' if date of findings or start date of events/interventions is between RFSTDTC and RFENDTC; 'FOLLOW-UP' if date of findings or start date of events/interventions is after RFENDTC.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Date/Time of Collection
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Collection date and time of an observation represented in IS0 8601 character format.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STDTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Start Date/Time of Observation
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Start date/time of an observation represented in IS0 8601 character format.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ENDTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: End Date/Time of Observation
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: End date/time of the observation represented in IS0 8601 character format.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DY
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Study Day of Visit/Collection/Exam
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Actual study day of visit/collection/exam expressed in integer days relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC in Demographics.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Relative study day between <--DTC> and DM.RFSTDTC. Add 1 if the difference is greater than or equal to 0.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STDY
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Study Day of Start of Observation
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Actual study day of start of observation expressed in integer days relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC in Demographics.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Relative study day between <--STDTC> and DM.RFSTDTC. Add 1 if the difference is greater than or equal to 0.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ENDY
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Study Day of End of Observation
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Actual study day of end of observation expressed in integer days relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC in Demographics.
BASEVARIABLE.Comments: Relative study day between <--ENDTC> and DM.RFSTDTC. Add 1 if the difference is greater than or equal to 0.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DUR
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Duration
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Collected duration of an event, intervention, or finding represented in ISO 8601 character format. Used only if collected on the CRF and not Derived.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --TPT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Planned Time Point Name
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Text description of time when a measurement or observation should be taken as defined in the Protocol. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See --TPTNUM and --TPTREF.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --TPTNUM
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Planned Time Point Number
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Numeric version of planned time point used in sorting.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ELTM
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Planned Elapsed time in ISO 8601 character format relative to a planned fixed reference (--TPTREF) such as "Previous Dose" or "Previous Meal". This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date/time variable, but an interval, represented as ISO duration.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --TPTREF
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Time Point Reference
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Description of the fixed reference point referred to by --ELTM, --TPTNUM, and --TPT. Examples: PREVIOUS DOSE, PREVIOUS MEAL.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --RFTDTC
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Date/Time of Reference Time Point
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Date/time for a fixed reference time point defined by --TPTREF in ISO 8601 character format.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STRF
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Start Relative to Reference Period
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Identifies the start of the observation as being before, during, or after the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ENRF
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: End Relative to Reference Period
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Identifies the end of the observation as being before, during or after the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --EVLINT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Evaluation Interval
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Evaluation interval associated with an observation such as a finding --TESTCD, represented in ISO 8601 character format. Example: -P2M to represent a period of the past 2 months as the evaluation interval for a question from a questionnaire such as SF-36.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STRTPT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Start Relative to Reference Time Point
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Identifies the start of the observation as being before or after the sponsor-defined reference time point defined by variable --STTPT.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --STTPT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Start Reference Time Point
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the sponsor-defined reference point referred to by --STRTPT. Examples: "2003-12-15" or "VISIT 1".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ENRTPT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: End Relative to Reference Time Point
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Identifies the end of the observation as being before or after the sponsor-defined reference time point defined by variable --ENTPT.

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --ENTPT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: End Reference Time Point
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the sponsor-defined reference point referred to by --ENRTPT. Examples: "2003-12-25" or "VISIT 2".

BASEVARIABLE.NAME: --DETECT
BASEVARIABLE.LABEL: Time in Days to Detection
BASEVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: The number of days from the start of dosing to the earliest detection of acondition or pathogen.

DOMAIN.STRUCTURE: One record per subject

VARIABLE.NAME: DMDY

VARIABLE.NAME: SVSTDTC

VARIABLE.NAME: SVENDTC

VARIABLE.NAME: SVDY

VARIABLE.NAME: SVSTDY

VARIABLE.NAME: USUBJID

VARIABLE.Comments: Concatenate STUDYID, SITEID and SUBJID, separated by "-".

VARIABLE.NAME: CMSEQ
VARIABLE.LABEL: Sequence Number
VARIABLE.Comments: Sort by the key variables specified in the domain list. Assign CMSEQ=1 to the first record and increment CMSEQ by 1 for each additional record so that CMSEQ is unique for each record within a USUBJID.

VARIABLE.NAME: CMTRT
VARIABLE.LABEL: Reported Name of Drug, Med, or Therapy

VARIABLE.NAME: CMDECOD
VARIABLE.LABEL: Standardized Medication Name
VARIABLE.Comments: WHODRUG Version 2010.09

VARIABLE.NAME: CMCLAS
VARIABLE.LABEL: Medication Class
VARIABLE.Comments: WHODRUG Version 2010.09

VARIABLE.NAME: CMCLASCD
VARIABLE.LABEL: Medication Class Code
VARIABLE.Comments: WHODRUG Version 2010.09

VARIABLE.NAME: CMSTDY
VARIABLE.LABEL: Study Day of Start of Medication
VARIABLE.Comments: Relative study day between <CMSTDTC> and DM.RFSTDTC. Add 1 if the difference is greater than or equal to 0.
